keyValuePair.Value: Is the team good enough to win the league?
There's always a real sense of expectation at this time of year. It looks like it could be a very competitive title race this season. Do you think your team can come out on top?
We set our own standards.
To be honest, this club is too important to go into a season hoping for the best. I think winning the league title is a requirement here. And part of our job is to handle those expectations.
It's about self-belief.
Confidence is so important. I think we have to aim to make a good start, build some momentum. Then self-belief will kick in and anything becomes possible as the season goes on.
These boys are winners.
I wouldn't swap my squad for anybody else's. Of course we're good enough. We should be challenging for the title every single year. Winning it is always our aim. We can't wait to get started.
Can your boys challenge for the title?

Everybody's making their predictions. It looks like a really exciting title race this year. How are you feeling? Do you think your team can be up there and really challenging in the league this season?
We always believe we can win.
I believe in these players and they believe in themselves. We go into every competition with the aim of winning it. The league will be no different this season. We're ready to give it a go.
We've enough ability, that's for sure.
This is a very talented group of players. Good enough, definitely, to win the league. But we'll need to be able to handle the expectations that come when you're playing for a big club like this one.
It's a very committed dressing room.

We're a very good team. I know there are other good teams in this league. But this group of players is special. They have incredible determination. They'll give everything to be crowned champions, I promise you.
Is there pressure on you to make the Champions League?
A lot of people are talking about your team at the moment. Your supporters expect to see you qualify for the Champions League this season. Do you think your team can handle that pressure?
We have to qualify, I think.

If you look at this club and think about its traditions, if you think about where we want to be in the future, then qualifying for the Champions League is absolutely essential. The players know what they have to do.
We'll have to cope with people's expectations.
Champions League qualification is seen as a minimum requirement for a club of this stature. It's vital so, of course, there'll be pressure on us all. We just have to be mature enough to handle it.
I'm confident we're good enough.

Of course it puts an extra weight of expectation on the players' shoulders. But I know they're good enough to play in the Champions League. I'm confident the boys can handle the pressure and get the job done.
Can you make Europa League this season?
We know you're trying to build something at the club. The supporters are excited about what's been happening. Can the team make it into the Europa League positions this season?
Europa League is the minimum target.
I think the supporters are right to be excited and we have to live up to their expectations now. For a club like this, Europa League should be the minimum that we aim to achieve this season.
We feel the pressure.
Of course the supporters are expectant and I think it's good for there to be some pressure on the players. Of course we should be aiming for a Europa League position this season.
European ambition will put the pressure on and I am confident that we can keep everyone happy.
We'll be competitive, for sure.
There'll be a few clubs fighting for the Europa League positions and I think we're ready to compete at that level, definitely. It'll be tough, but we'll be giving everything to achieve our aim.
Can you finish in the top half this season?
Of course, improvements don't happen overnight and there's a lot of work to be done at the club. But do you think the team's ready to avoid the embarrassment of a bottom half finish this season?
We have to be consistent.
This team's capable of getting good results. Our problem is consistency. We have to get out of the habit of making costly mistakes and letting games slip. If we do that, then we can move forward.
We want to be safe, first of all.

Before we think about a top-half finish, we need to make sure we don't get dragged into a relegation battle. All the teams down at the bottom will be fighting for their lives. We don't want to be one of them.
The players are good enough.
I think we've got a competitive squad at the club now. I think the boys know they're good enough to avoid getting into any trouble at the wrong end of the table. We're better than that.
Can your boys beat the drop this season?
There's a lot of pressure on your players. Everybody seems to be expecting you to struggle. Are you confident your team has enough quality to avoid relegation this season?
We're ready for the fight.

We have to believe we're good enough to survive in this division. It's going to be tough but the players are ready for the fight. If we can get a few good results early on, who knows what might happen?
We have to get enough points to survive.
We'll go out and try to win every game, I promise. But we're realistic. We know every point will be precious for us. Avoiding relegation is our target for the season.
The players are good enough.

I think there's a good feeling in our dressing room. We all believe we're good enough to stay in this division. It's going to be tough, we know that. But we want to prove we're a better team than people think.
Can you expect anything better than a bottom-half finish?
This could be a long and difficult season for you. The supporters seem to be expecting your boys to struggle. Is a scrap down near the bottom of the table all that you can see ahead for the team?
We'll go out and fight for every point.
This is an incredibly competitive division and we're under no illusions. We know we'll have to give everything in every single game. Let's fight for every point and see where we end up.
We have to stick together, don't we?

We definitely can't afford to be complacent. This is a very difficult league and, if we're going to make up for what we maybe lack in quality, we're going to have to give everything for one another every game.
I know we're good enough.
I'm absolutely sure we're good enough not to struggle this season. The lads have plenty of belief in themselves, too. But now it's about going out and winning games and proving people wrong.
Can you be in the promotion shake-up?
%1s are just one of several teams who think they can get promoted this season. It's going to be competitive. Are your boys good enough to go up?
That's our aim.
We definitely think we can push for promotion this season. We'll work hard every game and every training session, that's for sure. Going up is what we're all looking to achieve, after all.
We'll give it our best, I promise.
I know the fans are hoping we can do it this season. And we're as desperate for promotion as they are. I think we're good enough. Now, it's up to the players to go out and prove it in every game.
We'll be there or thereabouts.

I'm very happy with the quality we've got in the squad. The fighting spirit, too. I think everybody is ready for the challenge. We all believe we've got a great chance to take the club up this season.
How high can you finish this season?
The supporters are looking forward to the season and I guess you and the players are, too. What do you expect? Is the team good enough to finish towards the top end of the table?
We'll have to battle for every point.
I'm not going to make predictions. But I know these players are ready to go out and scrap for every single point this season. If we stick together, there's no reason we can't surprise a few people.
We have to be patient.

I think our attitude is going to be very important. We need to stay calm, believe in ourselves and be resilient when things don't go our way. We can build something worthwhile over the course of the season.
I think this team can compete against anybody.

I'm really happy with the group of players I've got to work with. We'll need every one of them to be ready to make a contribution. I think there's enough talent at the club for us to have a very good year.
Can your boys compete for the title this season?
It looks wide open this year. There are plenty of clubs around with big ambitions. How confident are you that your team can be one of those fighting for the title?
We'll have to work hard to have a chance.
There's definitely the talent in this squad to make a challenge for the title. The boys know how hard they'll have to work, though, if they want to be in with a chance this season.
We believe in ourselves.
We've put a very good squad together, I think. And we've worked hard to prepare properly for the new season. Now let's see. We hope we can be challenging for the title, that's for sure.
We're in with a great chance.
This is a very talented group of players and I think we all believe we can do something special this season. Winning the title? It's a big ask but I think we're in with a great chance.
Can you bring European football to the club?
The club is very ambitious and wants to be playing in Europe next season. Looking at the squad you've put together, do you think that's a realistic target for your team?
We have to prove ourselves now.
I think there's a sense of expectation around the club. These are exciting times and the players are hungry for success. We believe we're good enough but we have to prove that now.
We'll be patient.
I think this team's good enough to qualify for Europe. But it'll take a lot of hard work from everybody. We just have to go out and fight for every point. Let's be patient and see where it takes us.
This is an excellent squad.
I'm very confident about the team's prospects. We've got some talented players and a good spirit, too. This club should 100% be aiming to qualify for Europe this season.
Are you aiming for the playoffs?

It's a very competitive division and a relentless schedule. But you've made it clear that your aim is for %1s to make the playoffs this season. Are you confident your team's good enough to achieve that?
We'll be ready to give everything.

This division is never easy, of course. But the team's good enough to make the playoffs. We know it'll be a long, hard fight. But we're ready for that and believe we can do it. We can't wait for kick-off.
There's a good feeling around the club.
Everybody's excited about the new season kicking off. I think our supporters believe there's something good developing here. Definitely, we're good enough. Let's see what happens.
These players are good enough, for sure.

We've got some very talented footballers here and a squad that's deep enough to see us through a long season. Playoffs have to be our ambition but I actually believe we're good enough to win the thing.
